[I] A game of hide and seek played on a grid of boxes

[T] KBlackbox is a game of hide and seek played on a grid of boxes where the
[T] computer has hidden several balls. The position of the hidden balls can be
[T] deduced by shooting beams into the box.

[U] https://apps.kde.org/kblackbox/

